# Query Efficiency

Source: `Plans/18-ai-agent-manual.md` §5

## Golden rules

1. Never call API/DB inside `for` / `map` / `forEach`
2. Never query inside another query's callback — join or preload
3. Never render N rows that each fetch their own data — query once, pass props
4. List/detail endpoints return all data the view needs

## Patterns

```ts
// ❌ N+1
for (const bill of bills) {
  await supabase.from('bill_items').select('*').eq('bill_id', bill.id)
}

// ✅ Embedded select
await supabase.from('bills').select('*, bill_items(*), payments(*), customer:customers(id, name, phone)')
```

| Need | Use |
|---|---|
| One table, filtered | `.select()` + `.eq()` / `.in()` |
| Multi-table related | Embedded select `resource(*)` |
| Repeated complex SELECT | Postgres VIEW (RLS still applies) |
| Procedural / atomic multi-step | RPC / Postgres FUNCTION |
| Super-admin cross-tenant aggregates | `SECURITY DEFINER` — aggregates only |
| >3s / PDF / reports | BullMQ job |
| Hot rarely-changing reads | TanStack Query cache + Realtime invalidate |

## Frontend

- Never `useQuery` inside `.map()` JSX
- Hoist queries to page/route; pass data as props
- Prefer TanStack parallel `queries: [...]` over sequential awaits

## Self-check before PR

"How many DB queries when list has 100 items?" If ≥100 → rewrite. Target ≤3 per request.
